---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Wychwood Partners — Execution Discipline for Scaling Companies"
  description="Wychwood Partners helps growth-stage and PE-backed businesses improve control across operations, cash, and leadership cadence so they scale without losing grip."
>
  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(var(--brand-accent),0.08)_0%,rgba(var(--surface),1)_55%)]"></div>
      <div class="shell section">
        <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12 md:items-start">

          <!-- LEFT: Hero Text -->
          <div class="md:col-span-7">
            <div class="max-w-3xl">
              <p class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))] px-3 py-1 text-xs text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))] shadow-sm">
                <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[rgb(var(--brand-anchor))]"></span>
                Fractional • Interim • Full-time COO support
              </p>

              <h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[rgb(var(--text))] md:text-6xl">
                Execution discipline for scaling companies.
              </h1>

              <p class="mt-4 text-base text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
                Wychwood Partners designs operating systems for scaling companies — installing the metrics, decision rules, forecasting discipline, and leadership cadence that make execution predictable as complexity grows.
              </p>

              <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))] md:text-xl">
                Wychwood Partners works across three operating layers — operations, cash & forecasting, and leadership cadence — to improve control, visibility, and execution discipline as businesses scale.
              </p>

              <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
                <a
                  href="/contact"
                  class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] bg-[rgb(var(--brand-anchor))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:opacity-95"
                >
                  Book a call
                </a>
                <a
                  href="/services"
                  class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] border border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] transition hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))]"
                >
                  See how we work
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- RIGHT: Three-Layer Diagram -->
          <div class="md:col-span-5">
            <div class="mt-10 md:mt-0 border border-[rgb(var(--border))] rounded-[var(--radius-xl)] overflow-hidden">

              <div class="px-6 py-6 bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))]">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Operations</p>
              </div>

              <div class="h-px bg-[rgb(var(--border))]"></div>

              <div class="px-6 py-6 bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))]">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Cash & Forecasting</p>
              </div>

              <div class="h-px bg-[rgb(var(--border))]"></div>

              <div class="px-6 py-6 bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))]">
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Leadership Cadence</p>
              </div>

            </div>

            <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              When one layer weakens, control erodes. When all three align, execution holds.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Operating System Failure Signals -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Signs your operating system is starting to break</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            Most scaling problems are not strategy problems — they are operating system problems. A few signals tend to appear early.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Dashboards disagree</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Revenue, margin, and pipeline numbers change depending on who you ask.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Founders remain the decision bottleneck</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Important decisions still require escalation because ownership and rules are unclear.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Teams argue about numbers</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Different systems define key metrics differently.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Revenue grows but margins drift</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Operational visibility weakens as the business scales.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">AI initiatives stall</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Automation and AI struggle because the underlying operating definitions are inconsistent.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Execution becomes unpredictable</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Strategy is clear, but outcomes vary because execution systems are weak.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Operating Architecture -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Execution holds when three operating layers align</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            Scaling companies rarely fail because of strategy. They fail because the systems that convert strategy into execution break as complexity grows.
            Wychwood Partners focuses on three operating layers that restore control and predictability. These layers rely on a structured set of operating definitions — metrics, decision rights, and execution routines — that define how a company actually works as it scales.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Layer 1</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold">Operational System</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Clear metrics, ownership, decision rules, and execution routines that define how the company actually operates.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Layer 2</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold">Cash & Forecasting Discipline</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Driver-based forecasts and financial visibility that allow leadership to allocate capital with confidence.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Layer 3</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold">Leadership Execution Cadence</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Weekly rhythm, accountability loops, and leadership structures that ensure decisions turn into execution.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Who I Work With -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Who I Work With</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            My work most often supports private equity-backed portfolio companies, founder-led growth businesses, and investor-owned consumer platforms navigating scale, integration, or transition.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            Engagements range from interim COO mandates to hands-on operating partner support through the hold period — including post-acquisition integration, multi-site expansion, international buildout, and IPO preparation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Services -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between">
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">What we install</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Practical operating control that converts strategy into disciplined execution — without adding bureaucracy.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a href="/services" class="text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] hover:underline">View services</a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
          <a href="/services/operational-systems/" class="group card p-6 transition hover:shadow-md">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Operational systems</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Operating model, metrics, roles, decision rights, and execution routines.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">Learn more →</p>
          </a>

          <a href="/services/forecasting-frameworks/" class="group card p-6 transition hover:shadow-md">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Capital & forecasting</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Driver-based forecasting, pipeline confidence, and scenario planning.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">Learn more →</p>
          </a>

          <a href="/services/leadership-cadence/" class="group card p-6 transition hover:shadow-md">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Leadership cadence</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Weekly rhythm, accountability loops, and leadership team performance.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">Learn more →</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Common questions</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
            A few questions often come up when companies start looking seriously at operating discipline and AI readiness.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">What is an operating system in a company?</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              It’s the structure that defines metrics, ownership, decision rules, and execution routines. When these are unclear, scaling becomes unpredictable.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Why do AI initiatives fail in scaling companies?</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              AI relies on consistent definitions of entities, metrics, and workflows. If the operating model is ambiguous, automation simply amplifies confusion.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">What does a fractional COO actually install?</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Typically an operating system for the business: execution cadence, metric clarity, decision rights, and forecasting discipline.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold">When do companies usually need this?</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Most often during rapid growth, private equity transitions, post-acquisition integration, or when complexity starts to outpace leadership visibility.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Insights -->
    <section class="border-t border-[rgb(var(--border))]">
      <div class="shell section-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-3xl">Insights</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Frameworks and practical notes on scaling execution.</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/insights" class="text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] hover:underline">View all insights</a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          <a href="/insights/q2-plans-die/" class="group card p-6 transition hover:shadow-md">
            <p class="text-xs font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Latest</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold">Q2 is where plans go to die</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              January optimism is easy. The execution gap shows up in May. Here is why Q2 breaks more plans than any other quarter — and what to do about it.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">Read →</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/insights/metric-disagreement/" class="group card p-6 transition hover:shadow-md">
            <p class="text-xs font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">Insight</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold">When everyone in the room has a different number</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
              Metric disagreement is not a data problem. It is a definitions problem — and it compounds quietly until it becomes a crisis.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] group-hover:underline">Read →</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is an operating system in a company?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A company operating system defines metrics, ownership, decision rules, and execution routines so teams can operate consistently as complexity increases."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why do AI initiatives fail in scaling companies?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AI depends on consistent definitions of entities, metrics, and workflows. When those definitions differ across systems, automation amplifies confusion instead of improving execution."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What does a fractional COO install?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A fractional COO typically installs execution systems including operating metrics, decision ownership, leadership cadence, and forecasting discipline so strategy converts into predictable execution."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "When do companies typically need operating discipline support?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Companies usually need operating discipline when scaling complexity begins to outpace leadership visibility, often during rapid growth, private equity ownership, acquisitions, or geographic expansion."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "DefinedTermSet",
    "name": "Wychwood Operating Architecture Concepts",
    "hasDefinedTerm": [
      {
        "@type": "DefinedTerm",
        "name": "Operational Context Layer",
        "description": "A structured definition of business entities, metrics, ownership, and decision rules that creates consistent operational meaning across systems and teams.",
        "inDefinedTermSet": "Wychwood Operating Architecture Concepts"
      },
      {
        "@type": "DefinedTerm",
        "name": "Company Operating System",
        "description": "The set of metrics, roles, decision rights, and execution routines that define how a company actually operates as it scales.",
        "inDefinedTermSet": "Wychwood Operating Architecture Concepts"
      },
      {
        "@type": "DefinedTerm",
        "name": "Execution Architecture",
        "description": "The operating structure that connects strategy, operations, forecasting, and leadership cadence so organizations execute predictably.",
        "inDefinedTermSet": "Wychwood Operating Architecture Concepts"
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
